The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs

 Sudipta Chakraborty, 18, a resident of Tiffinbazar, in Belur, was run over by a truck on GT Road on Friday. Police said the first-year student was riding a bicycle defying traffic rules. The driver and the help have been arrested. In another mishap, a couple was seriously injured when a police van hit their motorcycle on BT Road on Thursday night. 

 A 40-year-old Bangur Avenue resident tried to commit suicide by jumping in front of a Tollygunge-bound train at Belgachhia Metro station on Friday morning. She sustained minor injuries. 

 Sanjay Chowdhury, in his late 30s, committed suicide by slitting his veins at his Entally residence on Friday morning. Police said the trader was suffering from depression. 

 More than 11,000 taxis, affiliated to Calcutta Taxi Association, will not ply on January 25 to protest hike in the third-party insurance premium for accident coverage from this year.

 Traffic movement on BT Road was disrupted for more than an hour on Friday morning, when workers of a jute mill blocked the road at Titagarh. 




